  "texts": [
    "This cautious approach ensured that potentially relevant studies were not prematurely excluded.The screening and selection of articles included in the review was carried out by a team consisting of the lead author (TAB), who has a background in behavioural and social sciences and has led and published articles using an SLR, a co-author (AB), who has a background in computer sciences and has published articles using the SLR, and two non-author, internal reviewers (JKK, IBJ) with a background in social sciences.",
    "Initially, the lead author and the two internal reviewers independently To filter articles discussing RAI, ethical, or trustworthy AI: the main elements of RAI practices today 3 AND \"transparen*\" OR \"fair\" OR \"accountab*\" OR \"bias\" OR \"accurate\" OR \"accuracy\" OR \"robust\" OR \"explainab*\" OR \"interpretab*\" OR \"secure\" OR \"security\" OR \"privacy\" OR \"benefic*\" OR \"explicab*\" OR \"justice\" OR \"non-maleficence\" OR \"controllab*\" OR \"diversity\" OR \"non-discriminative\"We used inductive reasoning to ensure the inclusion of all related keywords within our knowledge that might extract or were related to any RAI practices 4 AND \"manage\" OR \"practical\" OR \"in practice\" OR \"step\" OR \"organize\" OR \"organise\" OR \"activities\" OR \"frontline\" OR \"do\" OR \"how to\" OR \"document\" OR \"reproduceab*\" OR \"monitor\" OR \"practice*\"To filter articles that demonstrated practices of RAI, rather than RAI principles, concepts, or framework AND \"industry\" aTo filter RAI applications in an industry setting and exclude those without a clear application domain a Only used for Scopus and ACM digital database because PubMed database was already focused on an industry (i.e., healthcare) * Used as a wildcard character to represent one or more characters in a string Data extraction Categorisation of the suggested RAI practicesWe utilised content analysis with inductive coding when examining the suggested RAI practices described in the included articles.",
    "In contrast to deductive coding, which starts with a theoretical framework and codes against this framework, inductive coding starts by observing and exploring a topic in question, in this case suggested RAI practices, to look for similarities and patterns.",
    "The content analysis involved generating initial codes for each article and then collating codes with similar content into themes.",
    "This process was iterated until all similar content was grouped together."
